LayoutNode.Content: Nice post. Public needs to know that they should interview their Realtor. Most of the buyers use online sources to look for a house. Look at yourRealtor’s reviews on Zillow. Read them and see if they match who you like to work with. You will be married to them for some time and you haveto have a good chemistry. They need to be honest and knowledgeable of their market and not take everything personally. Do your homework.

LayoutNode.Content: I’ve been an Agent/Realtor/Property Manager/Broker for many years and one of the most difficult situations I’ve dealt with is Dual Agency. It maybe legal, but does that make it ethical? Not to me. If you were being sued would you hire the same attorney hired by the person sueing you? Or hirethe same divorce attorney as your soon to be ex?
